---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Section from "@/components/Section.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="A small, considered grooming studio in Santa Monica — with a soft spot for cats and the dogs who run the neighborhood.">
  <Section eyebrow="About" title="A studio built for the pet, first.">
    <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12">
      <div class="md:col-span-7 space-y-5 text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-black/80">
        <p>
          The Pet Affaire is a small grooming studio in Santa Monica. We started it because the
          pet-spa world had drifted somewhere noisy and impersonal — assembly-line bookings, hours
          in cages, hurried hands. We wanted the opposite: a quiet room, one pet at a time, and
          enough time to do the job properly.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most of what makes a good groom isn't the haircut. It's how the pet feels at the end of
          it. We work slowly, read the animal in front of us, and stop when stopping is the right
          call. We are honest about what your dog's coat will and won't do, and we'll tell you the
          truth when a mat is past combing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Cats get their own quiet windows — no dog noise, no rush, no stranger touching them
          before they're ready. We see one cat at a time, every time.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="md:col-span-5">
        <div class="aspect-[4/5] rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-[var(--color-sage)] via-[var(--color-bone)] to-[var(--color-rose)]"></div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Our promises" title="What we'll always do." bg="bone">
    <ul class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-black/75">
      <li><strong class="text-black">One pet at a time.</strong> No barking room, no kennel waits.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-black">Hand-dried.</strong> No drying cages, ever.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-black">Honest pricing.</strong> If a groom is going to cost more, you'll hear it before we begin.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-black">Welfare-first.</strong> If a groom isn't safe to finish, we stop and explain why.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-black">Cat-only windows.</strong> Quiet, dog-free, calm.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-black">Open communication.</strong> Real-time texts on arrival, mid-groom, and ready-for-pickup.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
